One person has died and four others were injured in a road accident involving a matatu and private car at Ekule on the Narok-Maai Mahiu road. A police officer at the scene said the private saloon car heading to Narok was negotiating a sharp bend when it veered out of its lane and collided with a Nairobi-bound Transline minivan from Kisii.The victim who died was a passenger in the saloon car. email print email print Kenya is lobbying against the planned agreement between US and 12 Asian states for fear of losingPeres will be buried next to Rabin, who was assassinated in 1995 by a Jewish extremist opposed to